1 1, 2026]: Sec. 14. On or before July 1, 2027, and each July 1
2 thereafter, Ivy Tech Community College shall provide to each
3 campus board an annual analysis of market labor outcomes that
4 does the following:
5 (1) Analyzes regional employer demand by sector, occupation,
6 and required skills.
7 (2) Quantifies campus level credential supply relative to
8 regional workforce demand.
9 (3) Identifies misalignment between program offerings and
10 high wage career opportunities.
11 (4) Considers other relevant data, as determined by a campus.
12 (5) Considers strategies to address gaps identified in
13 subdivisions (1) through (4).
14 SECTION 8. IC 21-22-6-15 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
15 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
16 1, 2026]: Sec. 15. (a) Each campus shall prepare a campus strategic
17 plan that connects with Ivy Tech Community College's strategic
18 plan and includes the following:
19 (1) The campus vision and mission.
20 (2) Measurable goals, including:
21 (A) overall student enrollment;
22 (B) enrollment in programs aligned to high wage, high
23 demand occupations within the campus service area as
24 identified in the campus strategic plan;
25 (C) student persistence, meaning a student's continued
26 enrollment and progress toward a degree or credential;
27 (D) completion of a high value credential or an associate
28 degree, or transfer to a four (4) year institution;
29 (E) placement into:
30 (i) work based learning; or
31 (ii) apprenticeships;
32 (F) job placement and graduate wages, as measured by the
33 regional good jobs definition approved by the campus
34 board under clause (H);
35 (G) building utilization; and
36 (H) a regional good jobs definition approved by the
37 campus board that includes consideration of:
38 (i) wages adjusted for regional cost of living;
39 (ii) access to employer provided benefits, including
40 health insurance and retirement;
41 (iii) opportunities for career advancement; and
42 (iv) positions providing significant public benefit,
