1 including early childhood education, health care, and
2 public safety.
3 (3) Specific strategies to achieve the goals identified in
4 subdivision (2), including:
5 (A) a general description of the actions the campus will
6 take to achieve each measurable goal;
7 (B) a target date for implementation; and
8 (C) a list of identified resources required for execution.
9 (4) A process for annual review and adjustment of the
10 strategic plan based on performance data and changing
11 regional conditions.
12 (b) The campus shall submit the strategic plan described in
13 subsection (a) to the campus board and state board of trustees for
14 approval.
15 (c) After a strategic plan has been approved under subsection
16 (b), the campus shall provide the campus board with a campus
17 budget summary and budget narrative that:
18 (1) demonstrates alignment between resource allocation and
19 the priorities, goals, and strategies identified in the strategic
20 plan;
21 (2) identifies categories of major expenditures;
22 (3) explains significant changes from the prior budget year;
23 and
24 (4) describes how budget decisions support the achievement
25 of measurable goals.
