2 SECTION 2, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 7. (a) Except as provided in subsection (b),
4 "workforce related program" means:
5 (1) a program operated, delivered, or enabled, in whole or in part,
6 by a state provider using public funds to offer incentives, funding,
7 support, or guidance for any of the following purposes:
8 (A) Job training.
9 (B) The attainment of an industry recognized certification or
10 credential.
11 (C) The attainment of a postsecondary degree, certificate, or
12 credential.
13 (D) The provision of other types of employment assistance.
14 (E) The promotion of Indiana to workers or the provision of
15 assistance to a worker relocating to Indiana for employment.
16 (F) Any other program that:
17 (i) has, at least in part, the goal of securing employment or
18 better employment for an individual; and
19 (ii) receives funding through WIOA or a state appropriation;
20 or
21 (2) a work based learning program or transitional jobs program
22 that is:
23 (A) through an employment social enterprise; and
24 (B) operated, delivered, or enabled, in whole or in part, by a
25 state provider using public funds.
26 (b) For purposes of IC 22-4.1-24-3, "workforce related program"
27 means a program offering incentives, funding, support, or guidance for
28 any of the following purposes:
29 (1) Job training.
30 (2) The attainment of an industry recognized certification or
31 credential.
32 (3) The attainment of a postsecondary degree, certificate, or
33 credential.
34 (4) The provision of other types of employment assistance.
35 (5) The promotion of Indiana to workers or the provision of
36 assistance to a worker relocating to Indiana for employment.
37 (6) Any other program that has, at least in part, the goal of
38 securing employment or better employment for an individual.
39 The term does not include includes an apprenticeship program for
40 which funding is received unless the apprenticeship program
41 receives funding under IC 22-4-25-1(c).
